category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
Liest du gerne? Stehst du auf Frauen? Liest du gerne frauenzentrierte Bücher? Dann bist du hier genau richtig!

Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, weil ich andere lesende Lesben und Bi-Frauen treffen wollte. Daraus ist ein kleiner Lesezirkel entstanden, in welchem wir alle das gleiche Buch lesen und danach besprechen. Manchmal schweifen wir auch etwas ab. Und immer haben wir es bei Essen und Trinken gemütlich. Ich bin gespannt auf dich!
name: Lesbischer Lesezirkel Thun

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

category.name: book clubs
description:
Liest du gerne? Stehst du auf Frauen? Liest du gerne frauenzentrierte Bücher? Dann bist du hier genau richtig!

Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, weil ich andere lesende Lesben und Bi-Frauen treffen wollte. Daraus ist ein kleiner Lesezirkel entstanden, in welchem wir alle das gleiche Buch lesen und danach besprechen. Manchmal schweifen wir auch etwas ab. Und immer haben wir es bei Essen und Trinken gemütlich. Ich bin gespannt auf dich!
name: Lesbischer Lesezirkel Thun

description:

I figured we can all exchange knowledge and experience in the subject so why not start a book-club style group? It would be really cool to get together and discuss.

So I took the group after the creator stepped down to keep it alive. I have some experience from theological studies to meditation and others but I just want this to be a collab effort and just share some good reads and stories.

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

description:

So I took the group after the creator stepped down to keep it alive. I have some experience from theological studies to meditation and others but I just want this to be a collab effort and just share some good reads and stories.

category.name: book clubs
description:
Liest du gerne? Stehst du auf Frauen? Liest du gerne frauenzentrierte Bücher? Dann bist du hier genau richtig!

Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, weil ich andere lesende Lesben und Bi-Frauen treffen wollte. Daraus ist ein kleiner Lesezirkel entstanden, in welchem wir alle das gleiche Buch lesen und danach besprechen. Manchmal schweifen wir auch etwas ab. Und immer haben wir es bei Essen und Trinken gemütlich. Ich bin gespannt auf dich!
name: Lesbischer Lesezirkel Thun

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!

description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)

― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!

description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

description: If you like reading and discussing ideas, we are a small group, meeting twice a month, to talk about a selected French book and its author. There a participation fee (for non-francophones) 20 Eur to cover teacher fees.   A minimum conversational French Level of B2 is preferred to allow for a fluid discussion.

description:

As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

description:
Hi everyone!
I figured we can all exchange knowledge and experience in the subject so why not start a book-club style group? It would be really cool to get together and discuss.

So I took the group after the creator stepped down to keep it alive. I have some experience from theological studies to meditation and others but I just want this to be a collab effort and just share some good reads and stories.

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
Liest du gerne? Stehst du auf Frauen? Liest du gerne frauenzentrierte Bücher? Dann bist du hier genau richtig!

Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, weil ich andere lesende Lesben und Bi-Frauen treffen wollte. Daraus ist ein kleiner Lesezirkel entstanden, in welchem wir alle das gleiche Buch lesen und danach besprechen. Manchmal schweifen wir auch etwas ab. Und immer haben wir es bei Essen und Trinken gemütlich. Ich bin gespannt auf dich!
name: Lesbischer Lesezirkel Thun
organizer.name: Annette

description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

description:

So I took the group after the creator stepped down to keep it alive. I have some experience from theological studies to meditation and others but I just want this to be a collab effort and just share some good reads and stories.

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

description:

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
Liest du gerne? Stehst du auf Frauen? Liest du gerne frauenzentrierte Bücher? Dann bist du hier genau richtig!

Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, weil ich andere lesende Lesben und Bi-Frauen treffen wollte. Daraus ist ein kleiner Lesezirkel entstanden, in welchem wir alle das gleiche Buch lesen und danach besprechen. Manchmal schweifen wir auch etwas ab. Und immer haben wir es bei Essen und Trinken gemütlich. Ich bin gespannt auf dich!

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart

description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

description:

I figured we can all exchange knowledge and experience in the subject so why not start a book-club style group? It would be really cool to get together and discuss.

So I took the group after the creator stepped down to keep it alive. I have some experience from theological studies to meditation and others but I just want this to be a collab effort and just share some good reads and stories.

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

description: If you like reading and discussing ideas, we are a small group, meeting twice a month, to talk about a selected French book and its author. category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

description:
Liest du gerne? Stehst du auf Frauen? Liest du gerne frauenzentrierte Bücher? Dann bist du hier genau richtig!

Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, weil ich andere lesende Lesben und Bi-Frauen treffen wollte. Daraus ist ein kleiner Lesezirkel entstanden, in welchem wir alle das gleiche Buch lesen und danach besprechen. Manchmal schweifen wir auch etwas ab. Und immer haben wir es bei Essen und Trinken gemütlich. Ich bin gespannt auf dich!
name: Lesbischer Lesezirkel Thun

I figured we can all exchange knowledge and experience in the subject so why not start a book-club style group? It would be really cool to get together and discuss.

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup

description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)

description:
Liest du gerne? Stehst du auf Frauen? Liest du gerne frauenzentrierte Bücher? Dann bist du hier genau richtig!

Ich habe diese Gruppe gestartet, weil ich andere lesende Lesben und Bi-Frauen treffen wollte. Daraus ist ein kleiner Lesezirkel entstanden, in welchem wir alle das gleiche Buch lesen und danach besprechen. Manchmal schweifen wir auch etwas ab. Und immer haben wir es bei Essen und Trinken gemütlich. Ich bin gespannt auf dich!
name: Lesbischer Lesezirkel Thun

category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

description:
Hi everyone!
I figured we can all exchange knowledge and experience in the subject so why not start a book-club style group? It would be really cool to get together and discuss.

So I took the group after the creator stepped down to keep it alive. I have some experience from theological studies to meditation and others but I just want this to be a collab effort and just share some good reads and stories.

category.name: book clubs
description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club

description: If you like reading and discussing ideas, we are a small group, meeting twice a month, to talk about a selected French book and its author. category.name: book clubs
description:
“... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.”
― George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones


There's something powerful about reading a beautiful piece of literature. This book club is for those who love to read both fiction and non-fiction books and are looking to have some fun, meet like minded people and just discuss literature (and perhaps movies based on our favorite novels).


If you have a book (poem) in mind that excites you and you would like to talk about it or just simply express your opinion about it, you are welcome to join us and let's discuss literature over some drinks. Or if you just love books and you'd like to hear what others are reading and talking about, or maybe you'd just like recommend your favorite reads, you are welcome. 


"Books loved anyone who opened them, they gave you security and friendship and didn't ask for anything in return; they never went away, never, not even when you treated them badly. ”

― Cornelia Funke, Inkheart
name: Constance Book Club Meetup
organizer.name: Rahab Meßmer

description: This is an intellectual group for anyone interested in exploring themes of feminism in an open and inclusive environment and who wishes to meet other feminists in the Zürich area. People from all religious, cultural and ethnic, and LGBTQ-identifying, backgrounds are welcome to attend. It is my hope that many different perspectives can come together to create enlightening and interesting discussions. <br>The overarching goals of this group are twofold, one: to discuss various bodies of literature (articles, essays, novels, non-fiction) with a feminist focus and two: to foster friendship amongst like-minded people who share a passion for feminist issues as they relate to society. Works discussed are aimed to be intersectional and inclusive. <br> Events can take different forms, aside from book discussions, to include fun social nights, film screenings, picnics, and other adventures. This is a supportive and inclusive group for like-minded badass women to build a feminist community, share ideas, and empower one another. Welcome!!
name: Zürich Feminist Book Club

description:
As the title of this group suggests, this is a book club and cafe meetup in Baden. Once a month we can meet to discuss a book we have picked and all read. In the meantime there will be chances for general meetups at cafes/restaurants around Baden for socialising and meeting new people.

At the moment this is just a book club for English speakers, however, if there are enough people we could also look at doing a German book club too.

Everyone should have a fair chance to select/suggest books they would like to the group to read, but if you are going to suggest "Fifty Shades of Grey" or something from Dan Brown... then this is not the book club for you. ;)
name: Baden Book and Coffee Club
